remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKPathBuilder` provides a mutable builder for constructing an <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPath> incrementally. Add contours, arcs, curves, and shapes, then call <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPathBuilder.Snapshot> to obtain a copy or <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPathBuilder.Detach> to transfer ownership of the path.

This type wraps a native Skia resource and implements `IDisposable`. Always dispose of it when done, either with a `using` statement or by calling `Dispose()` directly.

## Examples

```csharp
using var builder = new SKPathBuilder();
builder.MoveTo(10, 10);
builder.LineTo(100, 10);
builder.LineTo(100, 100);
builder.Close();
using var path = builder.Detach();
canvas.DrawPath(path, paint);
```
